%
% Use the cm font family instead of the ec fonts explicitly called
% for in the extsizes class files.  Originally provided by Phil
% Viton to solve the problem for the beamer class.
%
% ================================== begin PAV modification
% Mod by Phil Viton to allow using the dc fonts and
% the latex_ml format in Beamer with SWP. Note that if you update
% Beamer you will need to copy this file (beamerbasefont.sty.pav)
% to (and over-write) beamerbasefont.sty, which references the
% ec fonts rather than the dc fonts we use.
% Basically, this hack copies the \DeclareFontFamily and
% \DeclareFontShape lines from T1cmr.fd and T1cmss.fd  
% then we add, on the lnes declaring the largest font size
% used in "normal latex", ie <24.88>, some new declarations, namely
% 			 <29.86><35.83><42.99><51.59>
%
